I respect that.

365
00:19:32.588 --> 00:19:36.884
Hey. Will. Will. I'm really sorry
about my dad.

366
00:19:36.967 --> 00:19:40.680
But I want you to know I believe in you.

367
00:19:42.014 --> 00:19:44.141
And I made you a sandwich. Catch!

368
00:19:48.479 --> 00:19:50.439
Oops. Airball.

369
00:19:50.523 --> 00:19:51.524
Sorry about that.

370
00:19:53.442 --> 00:19:54.694
Don't even worry about it.

371
00:19:54.777 --> 00:19:57.947
I'll still see you at the Greenhouse
when you're playing for the Thorns!

372
00:19:58.030 --> 00:19:59.657
-Thanks. Theo.
-Good luck!

373
00:20:01.909 --> 00:20:07.123
-Yo. I told you that video was crazy.
-Yeah. that dude was guzzling.

374
00:20:07.206 --> 00:20:09.917
-Yo! What's up. my mammal?
-Hey.

375
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.210
-Hey.
-There he is.

376
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:13.963
Thanks for letting me crash at your place.

377
00:20:14.046 --> 00:20:16.716
You brought your stuff?
Hey. throw it on the pile.

378
00:20:16.799 --> 00:20:18.050
Still haven't cleaned.

379
00:20:18.134 --> 00:20:20.094
Okay. just pick a pile.
They're all filthy.

380
00:20:20.177 --> 00:20:23.389
Now quit your yapping and come check out
what I've been cooking up.

381
00:20:40.072 --> 00:20:41.407
You like that?

382
00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:43.492
Come on. this is gonna go viral.

383
00:20:43.576 --> 00:20:45.077
You broke his ankles.

384
00:20:45.161 --> 00:20:46.704
Yeah. and he broke my horn.

385
00:20:47.204 --> 00:20:50.916
Will. look. you wanted footage
of you playing against bigs.

386
00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:54.503
And you just went up against the biggest.
baddest in all of roarball.

387
00:20:54.587 --> 00:20:56.672
-Yep. yep. Facts.
-You did that. Will.

388
00:20:57.506 --> 00:20:59.300
Okay.

389
00:20:59.383 --> 00:21:03.471
Well. I'm just gonna make this one live
'cause I think Daryl just farted.

390
00:21:03.554 --> 00:21:04.680
I'll see you both later.

391
00:21:04.764 --> 00:21:06.807
I got a date. Need to shave.

392
00:21:06.891 --> 00:21:08.142
With who?

393
00:21:08.225 --> 00:21:10.019
I didn't tell you? Your mom.

394
00:21:10.770 --> 00:21:12.188
Oh. shoot.

395
00:21:12.271 --> 00:21:13.355
Yeah. she got you. bro.

396
00:21:13.439 --> 00:21:16.150
Okay. okay. Wasn't even funny.

397
00:21:16.233 --> 00:21:19.403
Hey. bro. Wanna play some Roar 2K?

398
00:21:19.487 --> 00:21:20.738
Nah. think I'm good.

399
00:21:20.821 --> 00:21:21.989
Should probably call it a night. you know?

400
00:21:22.072 --> 00:21:24.033
No. sure thing.
Yeah. make yourself comfortable.

401
00:21:24.575 --> 00:21:26.160
I'm gonna get on these sticks.

402
00:21:30.956 --> 00:21:31.957
Hello!

403
00:21:34.293 --> 00:21:35.503
Okay.

404
00:22:00.778 --> 00:22:02.029
It's him. look.

405
00:22:02.696 --> 00:22:04.782
Look. it's totally him!

406
00:22:07.910 --> 00:22:09.578
Hey! What's up. buddy?

407
00:22:10.913 --> 00:22:11.914
Hey. Will.

408
00:22:11.997 --> 00:22:14.250
-Hey. Will.
-Hi. anonymous animal.

409
00:22:14.333 --> 00:22:16.043
Look. Mom. It's Will.

410
00:22:16.126 --> 00:22:18.546
-I'm sorry.
-That's okay. It's okay.

411
00:22:23.759 --> 00:22:27.555
Yo. who is the clown
that parked like that outside?

412
00:22:28.806 --> 00:22:29.932
Everybody good?

413
00:22:31.976 --> 00:22:33.143
Why are y'all not blinking?

414
00:22:33.227 --> 00:22:36.188
That's me. sweetheart. I'm the clown.

415
00:22:36.272 --> 00:22:39.483
You're Florence Everson!
You're the owner of the Thorns!

416
00:22:39.567 --> 00:22:42.903
You can ignore all the voice mails.
Mr. Harris.

417
00:22:42.987 --> 00:22:45.322
It looks like I found you myself.

418
00:22:45.406 --> 00:22:47.157
She's been waiting for you.

419
00:22:47.241 --> 00:22:49.159
Without ordering anything.

420
00:22:49.660 --> 00:22:50.703
Sit.

421
00:22:50.786 --> 00:22:53.330
You had quite the game yesterday.

422
00:22:53.414 --> 00:22:57.084
You broke Mane's ankles so hard. I thought
they were gonna have to put him down!

423
00:22:57.167 --> 00:23:00.087
And the Internet just loved it.

424
00:23:00.671 --> 00:23:02.756
They love you.

425
00:23:02.840 --> 00:23:05.092
Yo! That's crazy!

426
00:23:05.634 --> 00:23:06.927
It gets crazier.

427
00:23:07.011 --> 00:23:10.431
Will. maybe you haven't noticed.
but the team is awful.

428
00:23:10.514 --> 00:23:11.515
Oh. no. We trash.

429
00:23:11.599 --> 00:23:16.478
We have the league's best player
and no path to the Claw. again...

430
00:23:16.562 --> 00:23:17.980
Small to small.

431
00:23:18.063 --> 00:23:23.903
I believe you are exactly what Jett
and this team needs right now.

432
00:23:23.986 --> 00:23:29.450
Goat. sure. But I think you might be
a two-horned unicorn.

433
00:23:29.533 --> 00:23:31.160
-Really?
-Yeah.

434
00:23:31.243 --> 00:23:34.079
I'd like to make you an offer.

435
00:23:34.580 --> 00:23:38.792
We need a sixth player to join the Thorns
for the back half of the season.

436
00:23:39.460 --> 00:23:42.963
Oh. my gosh. Is it really--
Is it finally happening?

437
00:23:43.047 --> 00:23:45.633
I just need you to sign here.
some initials here.

438
00:23:45.716 --> 00:23:47.468
and you're officially a Thorn.

439
00:23:47.551 --> 00:23:49.803
And Jett. She signed off on this?

440
00:23:49.887 --> 00:23:52.056
In many ways. it was her idea.

441
00:23:52.139 --> 00:23:53.682
Yeah. So what's it gonna be?

442
00:23:53.766 --> 00:23:55.643
Play for Vineland.

443
00:23:55.726 --> 00:23:58.395
or stay here and bus my table?

444
00:23:58.479 --> 00:24:01.106
Pen. Pen! Pen. Someone give me a pen!

445
00:24:01.190 --> 00:24:02.358
I don't have a--

446
00:24:03.150 --> 00:24:04.276
Thank you.

447
00:24:05.903 --> 00:24:08.113
W. H.

448
00:24:08.197 --> 00:24:10.783
Where there's a Will. there's a way.

449
00:24:10.866 --> 00:24:15.287
Congratulations. sweetie.
We're so proud of you.

450
00:24:15.371 --> 00:24:17.623
Willt Will! Willt Willt Willt

451
00:24:19.208 --> 00:24:20.459
I cannot believe it!

452
00:24:20.542 --> 00:24:22.628
I'm gonna be a Vineland Thorn!

453
00:24:22.711 --> 00:24:25.506
-Breaking news! Will. it went viral!
-You're not gonna believe it!

454
00:24:25.589 --> 00:24:26.715
It certainly did.

455
00:24:26.799 --> 00:24:28.384
I'm so excited. Will.

456
00:24:28.467 --> 00:24:29.843
Who's the fancy pig?

457
00:24:30.803 --> 00:24:32.888
I hate this town.

458
00:24:52.574 --> 00:24:54.535
It hurts. It hurts.

459
00:25:00.165 --> 00:25:02.084
Welcome to the Roar Roundup.

460
00:25:02.167 --> 00:25:04.044
I'm two-time champion. Chuck.

461
00:25:04.128 --> 00:25:07.047
alongside my cohost.
itty-bitty-bitey-buddy.

462
00:25:07.131 --> 00:25:08.507
-Rusty.
-Rusty!

463
00:25:08.590 --> 00:25:11.427
I can't wait till they put you
out to pasture. Chuck.

464
00:25:11.927 --> 00:25:15.514
That's good. Well. but back to
the question we ask every season.

465
00:25:15.597 --> 00:25:17.933
Can you be the GOAT
without winning a championship?

466
00:25:18.017 --> 00:25:20.436
-Yes. What is that?
-Let's face it. Claws make careers.

467
00:25:20.519 --> 00:25:21.645
-You don't say!
-Nuh-uh.

468
00:25:21.729 --> 00:25:23.814
I feel for Fillmore.
She's always been a great player.

469
00:25:23.897 --> 00:25:26.025
but Father Time catches up with everyone.

470
00:25:26.108 --> 00:25:28.444
Without me. they wouldn't
have anything to talk about.

471
00:25:28.527 --> 00:25:30.154
All stats. no Claws.

472
00:25:30.237 --> 00:25:31.905
But you can't put all the blame on her.

473
00:25:31.989 --> 00:25:35.325
Anyone who's watched this team and thinks
Jett's the biggest problem is blind as a--

474
00:25:35.409 --> 00:25:38.787
Blind as a what. Chuck? Say it.
Blind as a what?

475
00:25:38.871 --> 00:25:42.499
I am the all-time leading scorer
in Roar history.

476
00:25:42.583 --> 00:25:45.878
Speaking of the Thorns.
we've got some breaking news. Chuck!

477
00:25:45.961 --> 00:25:47.880
The Vineland Thorns have finally
signed a sixth player.

478
00:25:47.963 --> 00:25:49.798
Looks like they're finally
getting Jett some help.

479
00:25:49.882 --> 00:25:51.091
Yes! A crocodile?

480
00:25:51.175 --> 00:25:53.093
No. no. no. no. Bigger. A gorilla?

481
00:25:53.177 --> 00:25:55.054
-We go now to owner Florence Everson...
-That's what I'm talking about.

482
00:25:55.137 --> 00:25:56.472
...with an exclusive interview.

483
00:25:56.555 --> 00:25:59.266
We signed roarball's first small.

484
00:25:59.349 --> 00:26:00.768
A small what?

485
00:26:00.851 --> 00:26:02.478
We got a little...

486
00:26:02.561 --> 00:26:03.520
A little what?

487
00:26:03.604 --> 00:26:05.272
-...teeny...
-A what now?

488
00:26:05.355 --> 00:26:06.732
-...tiny...
-Come again.

489
00:26:06.815 --> 00:26:07.858
...goat.

490
00:26:08.859 --> 00:26:10.402
A goat?

491
00:26:26.919 --> 00:26:28.212
Not again.

492
00:26:28.295 --> 00:26:30.130
Florence Marjorie Everson!

493
00:26:30.214 --> 00:26:34.051
You're signing a goat?
Have you lost your mind?

494
00:26:34.134 --> 00:26:36.345
Okay. Excuse me.

495
00:26:36.428 --> 00:26:39.431
You're the one who asked for a team
who could win the Claw

496
00:26:39.515 --> 00:26:42.059
and you didn't care how. Remember?

497
00:26:42.142 --> 00:26:44.228
Well. I care about this.

498
00:26:44.311 --> 00:26:46.021
I can't play with a goat.

499
00:26:46.105 --> 00:26:47.981
He's an embarrassment to the team.

500
00:26:48.065 --> 00:26:50.150
He's an embarrassment to the city.
He's a--

501
00:26:50.234 --> 00:26:51.652
He's sitting right there.

502
00:26:53.112 --> 00:26:54.738
Hey!

503
00:26:56.490 --> 00:26:57.950
You gotta be kidding me.

504
00:26:58.033 --> 00:27:00.077
I couldn't even see him in the chair. Flo.

505
00:27:00.160 --> 00:27:01.662
How am I supposed to see him on the court?

506
00:27:01.745 --> 00:27:03.997
I'll be the goat in the Thorns jersey.

507
00:27:04.081 --> 00:27:05.082
You feel me?

508
00:27:05.165 --> 00:27:06.166
Uh-huh.

509
00:27:06.667 --> 00:27:08.377
Look away. Flo. I'm just gonna eat him.

510
00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:11.463
Yeah. I'm gonna eat him
with a side of ranch dressing.

511
00:27:11.547 --> 00:27:14.133
and we're gonna act like
none of this happened.

512
00:27:14.216 --> 00:27:15.634
I do not taste good.

513
00:27:15.717 --> 00:27:17.052
I thought you said she knew.

514
00:27:17.136 --> 00:27:19.471
It's my job to bend the truth. Will.
Come on.

515
00:27:20.514 --> 00:27:24.017
It's also my job to play the long game.

516
00:27:24.101 --> 00:27:27.604
This is generating more attention
than we have had in years.

517
00:27:27.688 --> 00:27:29.940
You don't want him on the court.
that's your call.

518
00:27:30.023 --> 00:27:32.442
But he stays on the roster.

519
00:27:33.110 --> 00:27:35.070
You must have lost your mind.

520
00:27:35.154 --> 00:27:36.989
Put your paw down.

521
00:27:37.823 --> 00:27:39.616
You should be elated.

522
00:27:39.700 --> 00:27:44.580
The stars have aligned perfectly
because the press is dying to meet Will.

523
00:27:44.663 --> 00:27:46.373
Will. down. Get down.

524
00:27:46.456 --> 00:27:48.750
-Okay.
-And I want you to introduce him.

525
00:27:48.834 --> 00:27:50.836
-No. Not happening.
-Yes. you are.

526
00:27:50.919 --> 00:27:53.505
They're actually waiting for you
right downstairs.

527
00:27:53.589 --> 00:27:55.841
So keep them tails up high. yes?

528
00:27:55.924 --> 00:27:59.011
Big smiles! Love you both! Now get out!

529
00:28:01.930 --> 00:28:03.473
Jett. hey.

530
00:28:03.557 --> 00:28:06.852
I just wanted you to know.
this is my dream come true.

531
00:28:06.935 --> 00:28:10.063
I mean. to play with you. like.
my favorite player of all time.

532
00:28:10.606 --> 00:28:12.357
I know I'm not what you expected.

533
00:28:12.441 --> 00:28:15.277
but I've spent my whole life
training for this moment.

534
00:28:15.360 --> 00:28:16.945
And if you just give me a sho--

535
00:28:17.029 --> 00:28:20.532
Look. kid. I saw your little viral video.

536
00:28:20.616 --> 00:28:22.701
Mane baked you like a birthday cake.

537
00:28:22.784 --> 00:28:26.121
Yeah. yeah. no. I'm gonna enjoy
watching the piranhas eat you alive.

538
00:28:26.205 --> 00:28:27.247
Jett! Jett!

539
00:28:27.331 --> 00:28:29.833
-Jett! Over here! Jett!
-Hey. Jett! Over here!

540
00:28:29.917 --> 00:28:31.251
-Willl Will!
-Will. over here!

541
00:28:31.335 --> 00:28:32.711
-Will!
-Will. over here!

542
00:28:32.794 --> 00:28:35.172
-Will. over here!
-Will. Will. Will!

543
00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:53.941
Let's get started.
Hardest questions first.

544
00:28:54.024 --> 00:28:55.984
Do you think going viral
in a playground entitles you

545
00:28:56.068 --> 00:28:57.277
to play professional roarball?

546
00:28:57.361 --> 00:28:58.528
Do you worry you'll let other smalls down?

547
00:28:58.612 --> 00:29:00.155
Aren't you just
a shameless publicity stunt

548
00:29:00.239 --> 00:29:02.074
to distract from another
Thorns losing season?

549
00:29:02.157 --> 00:29:03.158
Are you actually a goat?

550
00:29:03.242 --> 00:29:04.785
-Don't you just kinda suck?

551
00:29:04.868 --> 00:29:06.870
Sorry. Can you repeat the question?

552
00:29:06.954 --> 00:29:09.373
Hey. hey. One at a time. y'all.

553
00:29:09.456 --> 00:29:11.959
This boy is not even media trained. okay?

554
00:29:12.042 --> 00:29:14.211
So. Will. How does it feel
to be the first small ever

555
00:29:14.294 --> 00:29:16.004
to sign a professional roarball contract?

556
00:29:16.630 --> 00:29:19.675
To be honest with you.
it's all kinda surreal.

557
00:29:19.758 --> 00:29:22.803
I mean. last night I was fighting off
roaches at my best friend's crib.

558
00:29:22.886 --> 00:29:25.389
and now I'm playing for the Thorns.

559
00:29:25.931 --> 00:29:27.266
You shouldn't have said that.

560
00:29:27.349 --> 00:29:29.476
Will. we are getting word that
the roach community was pretty offended

561
00:29:29.559 --> 00:29:30.560
by your last comment.

562
00:29:30.644 --> 00:29:31.937
Would you care to issue an apology?

563
00:29:32.020 --> 00:29:34.189
Oh. gosh. No. no. no. no.
That's not what I meant.

564
00:29:34.273 --> 00:29:36.483
- love roaches.
-Lies.

565
00:29:36.566 --> 00:29:38.485
-Can we move on to the next question?
-Up here.

566
00:29:38.568 --> 00:29:41.113
So. Will. you're not at all concerned
about being hurt?

567
00:29:41.196 --> 00:29:43.198
Roarball takes its toll on
the toughest of bigs.

568
00:29:43.282 --> 00:29:46.118
I imagine for a small. it could be fatal.

569
00:29:46.660 --> 00:29:49.204
-Well...
-No. no. Will knows the risks.

570
00:29:49.288 --> 00:29:51.581
Could he be clobbered? Possibly.

571
00:29:51.665 --> 00:29:53.208
Crushed? Perhaps.

572
00:29:53.292 --> 00:29:55.127
Killed? Probably.

573
00:29:55.210 --> 00:29:57.629
But that's how much he loves the game.

574
00:29:57.713 --> 00:29:59.339
He'd die for it.

575
00:29:59.965 --> 00:30:02.301
-Right. Will?
-Right.

576
00:30:02.384 --> 00:30:03.468
What about Mane?

577
00:30:03.552 --> 00:30:05.345
Are you worried about a rematch
down the line?

578
00:30:05.429 --> 00:30:06.430
No. No way.

579
00:30:06.513 --> 00:30:10.726
We call this dude the horse whisperer.
'cause he broke that bronco's back. okay?

580
00:30:10.809 --> 00:30:12.352
You know what he was telling me earlier?

581
00:30:12.436 --> 00:30:13.979
He's got a nickname for Mane.

582
00:30:14.062 --> 00:30:16.398
He calls him "My Little Pony."

583
00:30:16.940 --> 00:30:18.442
-Don't you?
-No. I didn't say that.

584
00:30:18.525 --> 00:30:19.693
-You do.
- I did not say that.

585
00:30:19.776 --> 00:30:23.280
And he also said that Mane
definitely ain't the GOAT.

586
00:30:23.780 --> 00:30:26.116
and his hair is wack. too.
which I also agree with.

587
00:30:26.199 --> 00:30:27.326
He's dead.

588
00:30:27.409 --> 00:30:28.994
-Why are you doing this to me?
-Last question.

589
00:30:29.494 --> 00:30:31.121
This one's for Jett.
You're in year fifteen.

590
00:30:31.204 --> 00:30:33.248
The team's bringing on a goat
to solve its problems.

591
00:30:33.332 --> 00:30:35.542
Do you ever wonder
if it's time to hang it up?

592
00:30:35.625 --> 00:30:37.794
I'm not hanging up anything. okay?

593
00:30:37.878 --> 00:30:40.756
I feel great right now. playing some
of the best ball of my career.

594
00:30:40.839 --> 00:30:43.967
And please. I've played with every mutt
this league has to offer.

595
00:30:44.051 --> 00:30:49.806
My only concern is going out there
and doing what I gotta do to win the Claw.

596
00:30:49.890 --> 00:30:53.477
and nothing. and I mean nothing.
is gonna get in the way of that.

597
00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:55.604
Thank you. Bagels on the third floor.

598
00:30:55.687 --> 00:30:56.730
Jett. over here!

599
00:30:56.813 --> 00:30:58.523
Yeah. Cool.

600
00:30:58.607 --> 00:31:00.692
-Will!
-Do you have any comment?

601
00:31:00.776 --> 00:31:02.778
I can-- Okay. thank you.

602
00:31:03.278 --> 00:31:04.529
Bye.

603
00:31:06.281 --> 00:31:10.077
Coach Dennis. how do you plan
on utilizing the goat in the rotation?

604
00:31:10.160 --> 00:31:12.496
That's a great question. Well--

605
00:31:12.579 --> 00:31:14.581
Dennis. he's all yours.

606
00:31:14.664 --> 00:31:16.041
Hey. Jett. you got a second?

607
00:31:16.124 --> 00:31:18.752
I just wanted to go over these new plays.

608
00:31:19.878 --> 00:31:21.713
You heard me. We'll do it later.

609
00:31:22.756 --> 00:31:25.217
How you doing. kid?
Dennis Cooper. Pleased to meet you.

610
00:31:25.967 --> 00:31:28.637
I know you. Coach Dennis. It's an honor.

611
00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:30.514
Coach is a strong word.

612
00:31:30.597 --> 00:31:33.850
I'm more of an underpaid clipboard stand.

613
00:31:34.768 --> 00:31:36.144
But I keep trying.

614
00:31:36.228 --> 00:31:37.729
Let's get you suited up for the game.

615
00:31:37.813 --> 00:31:38.730
I'm ready to play.

616
00:31:38.814 --> 00:31:41.274
Play? I... That's cute. No.

617
00:31:41.358 --> 00:31:42.234
-What?
-Nothing.

618
00:31:43.110 --> 00:31:44.820
And here we are.

619
00:31:46.446 --> 00:31:49.408
No way. The Thorns locker room?

620
00:31:50.951 --> 00:31:52.244
Yes!

621
00:31:52.327 --> 00:31:54.788
Get dressed and come meet the team.

622
00:31:55.539 --> 00:31:57.666
Yes. yes. yes. yes!

623
00:31:57.749 --> 00:31:59.167
This is crazy!

624
00:32:02.212 --> 00:32:03.547
Yo!

625
00:32:04.339 --> 00:32:07.426
My name. On a Thorns jersey.

626
00:32:09.052 --> 00:32:12.013
Wait. Fillmore 13's?

627
00:32:22.732 --> 00:32:23.859
Not bad.

628
00:32:26.862 --> 00:32:27.904
Right?

629
00:32:31.408 --> 00:32:33.118
It's game night.

630
00:32:33.201 --> 00:32:36.913
Welcome back to
Regionally Organized Animal Roarball.

631
00:32:36.997 --> 00:32:39.291
The sport with the wildest courts.

632
00:32:39.374 --> 00:32:40.584
Stalactites.

633
00:32:40.667 --> 00:32:41.835
Sandstorms.

634
00:32:41.918 --> 00:32:42.752
Cliffs.

635
00:32:42.836 --> 00:32:43.712
Ice.

636
00:32:43.795 --> 00:32:45.505
Fire. And vines!

637
00:32:45.589 --> 00:32:47.466
Tonight. we're at the Greenhouse.

638
00:32:47.549 --> 00:32:49.384
and the stadium is rocking

639
00:32:49.468 --> 00:32:51.386
for the first
of three straight home games.

640
00:32:51.470 --> 00:32:56.183
And no surprise. the smalls have
shown up big for Vineland's newest Thorn.

641
00:33:00.687 --> 00:33:03.106
The Canoodle Cam is on patrol!

642
00:33:03.857 --> 00:33:05.775
Somebunny's in love!

643
00:33:05.859 --> 00:33:07.569
Looks like they're necking!

644
00:33:07.652 --> 00:33:10.322
"Polly want a cracker?”
Am I right. up-Chuck?

645
00:33:15.911 --> 00:33:16.912
You caught it!

646
00:33:18.163 --> 00:33:19.581
I'm a genius.

647
00:33:20.165 --> 00:33:22.751
Okay. Olivia. Clear your mind.

648
00:33:22.834 --> 00:33:24.127
I am in control.

649
00:33:24.211 --> 00:33:26.796
I know who I am. I am good enough.

650
00:33:26.880 --> 00:33:29.216
I do not care about
the opinions of others.

651
00:33:29.299 --> 00:33:32.052
I do not care what they're saying
about me online. right now.

652
00:33:32.135 --> 00:33:34.429
across multiple platforms
which I could check.

653
00:33:34.513 --> 00:33:35.805
just to see what they're saying.

654
00:33:35.889 --> 00:33:38.475
Phone! Phone. Does anyone have a phone?

655
00:33:38.558 --> 00:33:39.935
You're not even in uniform!

656
00:33:40.018 --> 00:33:41.978
Ha! It's tear-away.

657
00:33:42.062 --> 00:33:44.231
-Oh. Lenny.
-We're gonna get you!

658
00:33:45.106 --> 00:33:46.566
Daddy's a yeti!

659
00:33:46.650 --> 00:33:51.404
Listen. I celebrate your creativity
with the foam.

660
00:33:51.488 --> 00:33:55.951
but it's not okay to shoot Daddy
in the face. okay? Great.

661
00:33:57.077 --> 00:33:58.161
Cute kids.

662
00:33:58.245 --> 00:33:59.579
Yeah. I know. Right?

663
00:33:59.663 --> 00:34:02.666
Don't look now. but there's a baby goat
walking towards us

664
00:34:02.749 --> 00:34:05.085
with a weird smile on his face.

665
00:34:05.168 --> 00:34:06.670
I'm Will Harris.

666
00:34:06.753 --> 00:34:10.173
Ready to help the team win however I can.

667
00:34:10.799 --> 00:34:13.885
Look. a pre-game snack.

668
00:34:13.969 --> 00:34:16.638
Let me just unhinge my jaw.

669
00:34:16.721 --> 00:34:18.557
Please. please! No!
Don't eat me! Don't eat me!

670
00:34:18.640 --> 00:34:20.934
-It's the viral kid!
-He's sick?

671
00:34:21.017 --> 00:34:22.978
No. he went viral.

672
00:34:23.061 --> 00:34:27.482
Weird. I like it. Come. Dance.

673
00:34:27.566 --> 00:34:30.193
We're not doing your little dance. Modo.

674
00:34:30.277 --> 00:34:31.861
I kinda like it.

675
00:34:35.574 --> 00:34:38.201
What's with the egg?

676
00:34:40.161 --> 00:34:42.747
Don't let them control you.

677
00:34:44.791 --> 00:34:46.543
Roots run deep.

678
00:34:47.002 --> 00:34:48.712
Roots run deep.

679
00:34:48.795 --> 00:34:50.297
Roots run deep.

680
00:34:50.380 --> 00:34:52.674
It's really loud in here. right?

681
00:34:53.174 --> 00:34:56.511
Hey. Jett? Do you think I'll get
some playing time tonight?

682
00:34:57.971 --> 00:35:01.474
Introducing your newest Thorn.

683
00:35:02.183 --> 00:35:06.146
Coming in at a hot 5'7".

684
00:35:06.229 --> 00:35:07.939
from South Vineland.

685
00:35:08.023 --> 00:35:14.821
the Mane-slayer himself. Will Harris!

686
00:35:18.199 --> 00:35:19.409
Where'd he go? I can't see him.

687
00:35:19.492 --> 00:35:21.369
Will history be made tonight.

688
00:35:21.453 --> 00:35:24.372
or will he follow in
your underwhelming footsteps. Chuck?

689
00:35:24.456 --> 00:35:26.833
You suck. Rusty.
And yes. that was a bat joke.

690
00:35:26.916 --> 00:35:28.752
-Yeah! Let's go. Will!
-Yeah. Will!

691
00:35:28.835 --> 00:35:31.379
That's Will. right?
He kind of looks like a gerbil.

692
00:35:31.463 --> 00:35:33.214
Do you think Will's gonna play?

693
00:35:33.298 --> 00:35:35.842
I hope not. or we're gonna watch
that kid die on live TV.

694
00:35:35.925 --> 00:35:36.843
Gerald!

695
00:35:42.724 --> 00:35:45.644
-Great! Yes! There it is!
-Let's go. baby! Keep it up!

696
00:35:45.727 --> 00:35:47.479
Hey. Coach. when do you think
I might get in?

697
00:35:47.562 --> 00:35:51.733
-Just study the playbook. kid.
-End his bloodline!

698
00:35:51.816 --> 00:35:52.692
Story time?

699
00:35:52.776 --> 00:35:56.738
Yeah. Bring it in. Once. there was a play
called Eagle 24.

700
00:35:56.821 --> 00:35:58.406
I like this one.

701
00:35:58.490 --> 00:36:00.825
Anyone tired? I could sub in.

702
00:36:00.909 --> 00:36:02.118
- I could take a break.
-No.

703
00:36:02.869 --> 00:36:05.872
He's gonna be playing in the next game.
Trust me.

704
00:36:07.207 --> 00:36:08.333
We need a bucket here.

705
00:36:08.416 --> 00:36:11.169
Modo. hang out on the perimeter.
Space the floor.

706
00:36:11.252 --> 00:36:12.921
Do your thing.

707
00:36:13.004 --> 00:36:15.757
I always do.

708
00:36:16.675 --> 00:36:17.634
Ball! Ball!

709
00:36:17.717 --> 00:36:19.386
Ball! Ball! Ball! Ball!

710
00:36:19.469 --> 00:36:20.637
Ball! Ball!

711
00:36:21.846 --> 00:36:25.141
Hey. I actually noticed that the moose
always drives right.

712
00:36:25.225 --> 00:36:28.228
so if you just shift the defense a li--

713
00:36:28.311 --> 00:36:30.689
Who wants an acacia leaf break?

714
00:36:30.772 --> 00:36:31.898
I do!

715
00:36:34.609 --> 00:36:39.197
Tomorrow. history will be made.
and I mean it this time.

716
00:36:40.782 --> 00:36:41.991
Shake it off. Archie!

717
00:36:42.075 --> 00:36:45.412
-I got water. towels. emotional support.
-I'm covered.

718
00:36:45.495 --> 00:36:48.373
Three tough losses in a row
for the Vineland Thorns.

719
00:36:48.456 --> 00:36:53.002
And now they'll hit the road with a goat
who's yet to see a dime of playing time.

720
00:36:56.589 --> 00:36:58.007
Ouch.

721
00:37:09.728 --> 00:37:11.354
No days off. am I right?

722
00:37:11.438 --> 00:37:14.315
No. no. no. Nope.
This is a private practice session.

723
00:37:14.399 --> 00:37:17.318
Hey. watch this.
From the logo. Nothing but net.

724
00:37:20.488 --> 00:37:21.489
Lucky shot.

725
00:37:22.407 --> 00:37:24.200
Maybe. Bank shot.

726
00:37:25.702 --> 00:37:27.912
Should I play the lottery?
I'm feeling good today.

727
00:37:27.996 --> 00:37:29.748
Why are you here. kid?

728
00:37:29.831 --> 00:37:31.541
I want some playing time.

729
00:37:32.125 --> 00:37:33.251
Not happening.

730
00:37:33.334 --> 00:37:37.297
Let's shoot for it. Or are you scared
you're gonna lose to a goat?

731
00:37:39.257 --> 00:37:40.550
All right. Bet.

732
00:37:40.633 --> 00:37:43.261
Top of the stands.
hook shot off the glass.

733
00:37:43.344 --> 00:37:44.971
spin around the rim. in.

734
00:37:48.433 --> 00:37:50.393
Jett from downtown. Did it.

735
00:37:54.981 --> 00:37:56.316
Easy.

736
00:37:56.399 --> 00:37:58.026
Through the vines. in.

737
00:37:59.068 --> 00:38:00.403
Hot paws over here.

738
00:38:01.988 --> 00:38:03.364
Yeah. baby!

739
00:38:03.448 --> 00:38:04.449
What else you got?

740
00:38:04.532 --> 00:38:05.992
Off the top.

741
00:38:06.534 --> 00:38:07.577
in.

742
00:38:14.918 --> 00:38:16.294
Hanging from the lights.

743
00:38:17.504 --> 00:38:18.838
Easy.

744
00:38:25.178 --> 00:38:27.055
You are mine now.

745
00:38:29.516 --> 00:38:34.312
From the tunnel. over the backboard.
nothing but net. All right?

746
00:38:34.395 --> 00:38:38.650
If I hit this one.
you have to give me playing time.

747
00:38:39.442 --> 00:38:41.236
Okay. yeah. We'll see.

748
00:38:42.278 --> 00:38:43.279
Pack it up.

749
00:38:46.658 --> 00:38:47.659
You missed.

750
00:38:48.201 --> 00:38:51.287
Come on. we gotta fly. Plane leaves in 30.

751
00:39:02.757 --> 00:39:04.884
I really had to hustle back there. but...

752
00:39:04.968 --> 00:39:07.136
Yo! What?

753
00:39:07.220 --> 00:39:08.304
We're on a PJ?

754
00:39:10.723 --> 00:39:12.392
What? Sick.

755
00:39:12.475 --> 00:39:15.103
-Are you seeing this? Oh. no.
-You got dunked on!

756
00:39:15.186 --> 00:39:16.396
Are y'all playing Roar 2K?

757
00:39:16.479 --> 00:39:19.649
They've added memes?
I mean. why would they do that?

758
00:39:19.732 --> 00:39:21.109
It's so disrespectful!

759
00:39:21.192 --> 00:39:23.862
Not just to me. but to all birds.

760
00:39:23.945 --> 00:39:27.615
Auntie Olivia is not giving bird.
Birds fly.

761
00:39:27.699 --> 00:39:28.908
Are you broken?

762
00:39:28.992 --> 00:39:34.622
Hey. hey. Auntie Olivia has a condition
called flightless bird syndrome.

763
00:39:35.123 --> 00:39:37.750
Auntie Olivia can't fly.

764
00:39:37.834 --> 00:39:40.962
-But we can!
-Oh. no! Not the cockpit!

765
00:39:41.045 --> 00:39:42.130
Girls!

766
00:39:42.213 --> 00:39:45.341
-We're taking over this plane!
-Reporting for duty!

767
00:39:45.425 --> 00:39:47.760
-No. don't touch that!
-At least the bags are comfy.

768
00:39:47.844 --> 00:39:50.138
-Hey. Lenny. Is this seat taken?
-Yep.

769
00:39:50.221 --> 00:39:52.432
-By who?
